{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17521993","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17521993"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T14:39:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T14:39:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13791"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17583784","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17583784"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:28:50+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:28:50+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13791"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"13791","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/13791"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.14,0.68,0.06,0.07,0.06]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6409"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92266"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6409","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6409"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13791"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75565"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"476"},{"type":"tags","id":"1254"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"12623"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31325"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92266","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/92266"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 18-year-old man presents to his General Practice clinic with a five-day history of sore throat and fatigue. He denies any recent travel or sick contacts. He has no significant medical history and does not take any regular medications.  He lives with his boyfriend, their extended family and their 3 cats in a two-bedroom apartment. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears tired but not acutely unwell. His vital signs are within normal limits. Oropharyngeal examination reveals tonsillar enlargement with exudates (Image 1). There is a tender, enlarged lymph node (2 cm) palpable in the left anterior cervical chain (Image 2). The liver edge is palpable 2 cm below the costal margin.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Streptococcal pharyngitis","Infectious mononucleosis","Cytomegalovirus infection","Toxoplasmosis","Acute HIV infection"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe clinical presentation in this case is highly suggestive of \u003Cstrong\u003Einfectious mononucleosis\u003C/strong\u003E. The classic triad of symptoms includes sore throat, fatigue, and cervical lymphadenopathy, which are all present in this young adult patient. Additionally, the presence of tonsillar exudates and hepatomegaly further support this diagnosis. Infectious mononucleosis is most commonly caused by the Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) and typically affects adolescents and young adults.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStreptococcal pharyngitis\u003C/strong\u003E can present with sore throat and cervical lymphadenopathy, but it usually has a more acute onset and is less likely to cause significant fatigue or hepatomegaly. It is also more common in children than young adults.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECytomegalovirus infection\u003C/strong\u003E can cause a mononucleosis-like syndrome, but it is less common than EBV as a cause of infectious mononucleosis. The clinical presentation is often less dramatic, with milder pharyngitis and less prominent lymphadenopathy.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EToxoplasmosis\u003C/strong\u003E can occasionally present with lymphadenopathy and fatigue in association with cats, but sore throat and tonsillar exudates are not typical features. It is also less common in immunocompetent individuals.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAcute HIV infection\u003C/strong\u003E can present with similar symptoms, including sore throat, fatigue, and lymphadenopathy. It is important not to make assumptions based on patient\u0027s sexuality. However, it is typically accompanied by other symptoms such as fever, rash, and myalgias, which are not mentioned in this case. The lack of risk factors also makes this diagnosis less likely.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Infectious mononucleosis typically presents with sore throat, fatigue, and cervical lymphadenopathy in young adults.","The Epstein-Barr virus is the most common cause of infectious mononucleosis.","Differential diagnosis of infectious mononucleosis includes streptococcal pharyngitis, cytomegalovirus infection, and toxoplasmosis."],"references":["Dunmire SK, Hogquist KA, Balfour HH. Infectious Mononucleosis. Curr Top Microbiol Immunol. 2015;390(Pt 1):211-40. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4670567/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"75565"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13791"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20732"},{"type":"media","id":"20733"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"20732","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20732"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/E8vsEMk5CEshsnr5vGdQ4QrgfbIb78.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.